          <msContents>
            <summary>[p]Written in a neat French gothic script, capitals picked out in red.[/p]
[p][b]Contents[/b][/p]
[p]1. ff. 1r-8v Anonymous astrological-divinatory text[/p]

[p]A fortune-telling game which matches 12 birds to zodiacal signs ff. 1r-7r, followed by instructions for playing the game ff. 7v-8v. On f. 1r are sketches of birds with names, and the qualities associated with each bird, and the zodiacal sign. One of the birds is a bat, classified as a bird in medieval encyclopedias[/p]

[p]Incipit f. 1v: 'Viues competenter nec queras amplius...'[/p]

[p]Explicit: '...deinde divide per 30 partes equales et quod remanebit erit numerus expartem'.[/p]
</summary>
